<DocsPageTitle Path="Migration">
    Blazorise 2.0 Migration CLI
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    The Blazorise Migrator is a command-line tool that helps you safely and predictably upgrade existing projects to Blazorise 2.0.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    It inspects your solution or project, reports the required changes, and can automatically apply them when you are ready.
    You stay in control at every step.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Installation
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader>
        Install the migrator as a global .NET tool from NuGet.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationInstallExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Verify installation">
        Confirm that the tool is available on your system path.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationSmokeTestExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Recommended workflow
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader>
        Follow this workflow to ensure a safe and reviewable migration.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>

    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <OrderedList>
            <OrderedListItem>
                Run <Code>analyze</Code> to understand which projects and files will be affected.
            </OrderedListItem>
            <OrderedListItem>
                Use <Code>--json</Code> to save the analysis report for later review or sharing.
            </OrderedListItem>
            <OrderedListItem>
                Run <Code>migrate</Code> with <Code>--dry-run</Code> to preview all file changes.
            </OrderedListItem>
            <OrderedListItem>
                Re-run <Code>migrate</Code> with <Code>--backup</Code> to apply changes and keep <Code>.bak</Code> copies.
            </OrderedListItem>
        </OrderedList>
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationExamplesExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Analyze
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Inspect your solution">
        Analyze a solution or project to determine required Blazorise 2.0 changes.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>

    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <Paragraph>
            The <Code>analyze</Code> command always runs in dry-run mode and never modifies files.
            It reports all detected migration actions before any changes are applied.
        </Paragraph>

        <Paragraph>
            If <Code>--path</Code> is omitted, the current directory is used.
            You may specify a folder, <Code>.sln</Code>, <Code>.slnx</Code>, or <Code>.csproj</Code>.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationAnalyzeCommandExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Migrate
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Apply changes">
        Apply Blazorise 2.0 migration changes to eligible projects.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>

    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <Paragraph>
            The <Code>migrate</Code> command updates projects that reference Blazorise packages.
            Use <Code>--dry-run</Code> to preview changes and <Code>--backup</Code> to preserve original files.
        </Paragraph>

        <Paragraph>
            If <Code>--path</Code> is omitted, the current directory is used.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationMigrateCommandExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Command options
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsAttributes Title="Analyze options" Ordered="false">
    <DocsAttributesItem Name="--path &lt;path&gt;" Type="string" Default="current directory">
